sentences.en: Her clothes were simple and unnoticeable.
sentences.cn: 她衣着简朴,不引人注目.

sentences.en: Strategic Code Splicing might have a minimal effect, but it's unnoticeable in almost all cases.
sentences.cn: 代码拼接有很小的影响, 但是大多数情况下都注意不到.

sentences.en: The orange wallpaper at the back of the hall is unnoticeable.
sentences.cn: 大厅后面的橘色墙纸不很显眼.

sentences.en: They might kill people slowly in a way that's unnoticeable, taking effect over perhaps 10 - 30 years by accelerating degenerative diseases.
sentences.cn: 它们可能用不引人注意的方式缓慢地杀害人民，促进退化性疾病也许在10-30年生效。

trans.tran_en: not easily seen or detected; imperceptible
